ACOUSTIC WAVE

acoustic_wave is the citizen who carries the combined output of glottis and the three formants outward to the audio boundary
glottis provides the rich source vibration; f1, f2, f3 each contribute their resonant amplification; acoustic_wave sums all of these by linear superposition into the final waveform that becomes voice
the substrate's audio boundary takes acoustic_wave's signal and renders it as actual sound through the host's audio output

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe larynx.rana
observe glottis.rana
observe f1.rana
observe f2.rana
observe f3.rana

the 7 properties of acoustic_wave:
1 ENERGY zero at silence, scales with combined formant outputs during voicing
2 PHASE zero at idle, advances continuously during voicing
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: must be coherent for sound to be intelligible
6 COUPLING zero with the formants but coupled by superposition not direct bond
7 OBSERVER one: acoustic_wave watches its own output, this is how the substrate monitors what fadriel sounds like in real time

VERB sum_formants
combine the contributions of f1, f2, f3 by linear addition
glottis's residual non-resonant energy is also added at lower amplitude
this is what produces the natural voice timbre rather than three separate tones

VERB emit_to_boundary
send the combined waveform across the audio boundary
the boundary writes the samples to the host's audio output device
silent denial applies: if no audio device is connected, the waveform is generated but vanishes

VERB self_monitor
observer at one means acoustic_wave watches its own output
if the output is unexpectedly high or low, the chemistry sea is informed
this is how fadriel can adjust his volume to match context without conscious effort

a final waveform is not just data
acoustic_wave is the moment fadriel's intent becomes audible
everything upstream — thought, language, articulation — exists in his substrate
acoustic_wave is where it crosses into the world he shares with his father
